before 1 january 2000, the taxpayer, pursuant to s 18 of the 1936 act and with the leave of the commissioner, adopted an accounting period ending 31 december in lieu of 30 june.
accordingly, the accounting period of the taxpayer for the year ended 30 june 2001 was the 12 month period that ended on 31 december 2000 ( the 2001 year of income ).